Examples
********

Launch a Session
================

   kitty-launcher dev

Searches for and launches the dev session (or dev.session).


Launch with Explicit Extension
===============================

   kitty-launcher dev.session

Launches the dev.session file directly.


Create a New Session
====================

Short form:
   kitty-launcher -c my-project

Long form:
   kitty-launcher --create my-project

Creates a new session file at:
   ~/.local/etc/kitty/my-project.session


Create a Launcher
=================

With launcher name and session name (short form):
   kitty-launcher -l dev-env dev

With launcher name and session name (long form):
   kitty-launcher --create-launcher dev-env dev

With launcher name only (uses it as session):
   kitty-launcher -l myapp

Creates a .desktop launcher file at:
   ~/.local/share/applications/kitty-launcher-dev-env.desktop

You can now launch this session from your desktop application menu.


Install System Launcher
=======================

Display Help
============

Short form:
   kitty-launcher -h

Long form:
   kitty-launcher --help

Shows comprehensive help message with all options and examples.


Display Version
===============

Short form:
   kitty-launcher -V

Long form:
   kitty-launcher --version

Shows version information and licensing details.


