Use Cases
*********

Perfect for Multiple Scenarios

Web Developers
==============

Managing multiple environments:

   kitty-launcher -c frontend     # Node.js, npm, linting
   kitty-launcher -c backend      # Python/Django, database tools
   kitty-launcher -c devops       # Docker, CI/CD deployment

Create visual launchers:

   kitty-launcher -l "Frontend" frontend
   kitty-launcher -l "Backend" backend
   kitty-launcher -l "DevOps" devops

Result: Click icon on desktop → terminal launches with full environment configured


System Administrators
=====================

Managing remote environments and tool configurations:

   kitty-launcher -c prod-access      # Production SSH with restricted tools
   kitty-launcher -c staging-debug    # Staging environment with debuggers
   kitty-launcher -c monitoring       # Log aggregation, metrics, alerting

Never accidentally deploy to wrong environment. Each launcher pre-configures:
   • Correct credentials
   • Right region/cluster
   • Appropriate tool access level
   • Audit logging enabled


Data Scientists
===============

Managing analysis and training environments:

   kitty-launcher -c analysis         # Jupyter, pandas, exploration
   kitty-launcher -c gpu-training     # CUDA, PyTorch, model training
   kitty-launcher -c visualization    # Plotting tools, dashboards

Quick context switching between analysis, training, and presentation modes.


KDE Plasma Desktop Integration
===============================

Combine with folder view widget for visual environment access:

1. Create launchers:
      kitty-launcher -l "Dev Project" dev
      kitty-launcher -l "Staging" staging
      kitty-launcher -l "Production" production

2. Add folder view to desktop: ~/.local/share/applications/

3. Hover over folder → cascading menu shows all launchers

4. Click launcher → terminal opens with that environment

Result: Visual desktop access to all configured terminal environments


